<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.35.24.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<fw type="letterhead">University of Missouri
COLUMBIA, MISSOURI 65201

COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE
Department of English

231 Arts  Science
Area 314 449-9756</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>February 27, 1971
</dateline>
<address>
<addrLine>Dr. John Neihardt</addrLine>
<addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine>
<addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska
</addrLine>
</address>
<salute>Dear John:</salute>
</opener>

<p>I can't tell you adequately how much pleased I was to receive a copy of <hi rend="underline">The Wonder of It
All</hi>. I have admired you and your work for a long time, and I am delighted to have your poetry where I am able to enjoy it again and again in your own reading.</p>
<p>I am also most grateful for your interest in Ted. He looks upon his work in Epic America as a high point in his college career -- but of course many of our students have felt the same way about it.</p>
<p>Thank you again for your most thoughtful gift. I hope that I will get to see when you are next in Columbia. In the mean time best wishes to you.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Cordially</salute>
<signed>Edward N. Weatherly</signed>
<note></note>
</closer>

</div1>
